    narr:narration """This hub catalogs phrasing assessments across organizational artifacts, mapping the transition from technical documentation to high-stakes strategic idiolect. The [core rubric assessment](narr:RubricAssess_Phrasing) establishes a baseline of 'narrative architecture' and 'steering vector' as canonical metaphors, while [GTM-focused assessments](narr:RubricAssess_Phrasing_GTM) and [IP-crisis analysis](narr:Assessment_Phrasing_IPCrisis) highlight the use of signature phrases like 'IP as code' to drive strategic alignment. A distinct idiolect emerges in [ADR-specific reviews](narr:RubricAssess_Phrasing_ADR002), which prioritize 'worldview layer' and 'strategy-execution disconnect' as shorthand for complex organizational states. In contrast, [technical documentation assessments](narr:Assess_Phrasing_cm) and [collective memory records](narr:Assess_Phrasing_collective_memory) maintain a flatter, functional register, relying on domain-specific terminology like 'Snapshot' and 'Transaction' without the branded metaphor clusters found in executive or customer-facing transcripts. The [customer architect's phrasing](narr:Assessment_Phrasing_CustomerArchitect) bridges these worlds, blending technical verbs with idiomatic, conversational markers.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#Assess_Phrasing_cm> ;
